post_text:
We hope you will be able to join us at our first FFA Foundation meeting of the year on Tuesday, August 20th at 6:00 p.m. in the Marceline Ag building.

The Marceline FFA Foundation is open to everyone that has an interest in the Marceline FFA and the Marceline Agriculture Department and there are currently no dues required for membership. At our last meeting it was discussed and decided to put three meeting dates on the calendar for the 2019-2020 school year. The first of those meetings as mentioned above will be Tuesday, August 20th, and the others are scheduled for November 25, and April 27, 2020.

post_text:
Convention day two is over. Here are some highlights:

-Rhiannon Niemeier, Sevilla Bussman, and Madison Gerdes performed a lively performance of "Riptide" at the Career Fair while our chapter and guests cheered them on.
-Rhiannon Niemeier and Luke Vaughn received their Missouri FFA State Degrees. Each Chapter can send 7% of its membership each year for consideration, but only 3% of the Missouri state membership will receive this degree and honor each year.

Students toured the career fair making connections with businesses and colleges. After that we had some lunch/mall shopping time, and then we ate at Five Guys for supper. That night we were privileged to be able to listen to guest speaker and Vietnam Veteran Dave Roever speak. A Purple Heart recipient himself, he taught students and guests about overcoming obstacles and included humor throughout. We then cheered on our State FFA Degrees and ended the night with Sonic icecream.

post_text:
Highlights from Day One of State FFA Convention:

-The Entomology team (Heather Darling, Ian Hochstetler, Payton Harris, and Hayden Krumpelman) placed 16th in the entire state of Missouri! Great job to all on your hard work!!

-Heather Darling received a Group I rating, placing 20th out of 182 Entomology contestants

-Brayden King and Veronica Vaughn served as voting delegates for our FFA Chapter at the state level.

Aside from competition, we also attended leadership sessions. We were able to listen to Shea Booster the National FFA Western Region VP, Margie Vandeven the Missouri Commissioner of Education, Christopher R. Daubert the Vice Chancellor and Dean of CAFNR at Mizzou, and various talent performances. Additionally, students were inspired with new SAE ideas watching the proficiency results. We celebrated throughout the day with a chapter meal at HuHots and Andy's and a pizza/pool party at the hotel prior to lights out.

post_text: Luke Vaughn has been selected to attend the 2019 MO HYPE Academy June 26-28th at the University of Missouri. This highly selective academy only selects 30 Junior Ag education students from all across the State of Missouri to attend. Each candidate is judged on an extensive written application process to be selected including five narrative responses, academic transcripts, FFA member activity forms, and three letters of recommendation. These 30 FFA members selected will receive hands on experiences to prepare them to communicate, lead and advocate for the agricultural industry. In addition, they will gain strategies to continue strengthening their knowledge base in agricultural issues, sharpen their written and verbal communication skills and spark potential career interests. Most importantly, they will bring home tools to help other members in their FFA chapters tell the agriculture story. This prestigious honor is a great way to represent Marceline FFA at the state level!

post_text: Veronica Vaughn was selected to the HYMAX (Helping Youth Maximize their Agricultural eXperience) Academy. It is a week long leadership conference this summer at the Lake of the Ozarks. Only 100 Freshman from all across the state of Missouri are selected to attend though a competitive written application process. These FFA members will be prepared for future leadership roles, agricultural career exploration, and advocacy for agriculture. In addition, they will gain key strategies for SAE development, written and verbal communication skills, and career development. Most importantly, they bring home tools to help their chapters achieve greater success! Congratulations Veronica on this huge honor and accomplishment!

post_text: The Marceline FFA Trap Team has exciting news! Last fall I filled out the Midway USA Grant on behalf of the Marceline FFA Trap Team. post_text:
Monday night, March 4th, were the Area III FFA Officer Interviews. The 24 schools from our area, Area III, can bring one candidate and two voting delegates each. Our chapter's candidate was Luke Vaughn and our two voting delegates were Kenzee Gladbach and Abbey Wright.

Luke completed in two rounds of interviews in front of room filled with 40+ delegates, 10 current Area III Officers (including Rhiannon Niemeier), and multiple advisors from Area III. At the end of the night he was selected to serve as the Area III FFA Chaplin for the 2019-20 year. Only 10 students from Area III make up this Area III Officer Team, so this is a huge accomplishment! If you see him please congratulate him on this honor and opportunity to represent our FFA chapter as a leader at the area level.

post_text: The results are in: Marceline FFA has TWO State FFA Degrees this year! Congratulations to Luke Vaughn and Rhiannon Niemeier for being selected to receive their State FFA Degrees. Each chapter can send up to 7% of their FFA chapter numbers for consideration each year. Only 3% of the ENTIRE FFA Missouri membership will receive this honor. State Degrees are based on the students' SAE (Supervised Agricultural Experience) and Leadership activities throughout FFA, their schools, and their communities. Both Rhiannon and Luke will walk across stage at the MO FFA State Convention April 25-26th to receive their degree plaques. Great job to them both! If you see either of them please congratulate them!

post_text:
Marceline FFA would like to send a cordial thank you to all that attended our Marceline FFA Food for America Barnyard Zoo on last Thursday, Feb. 21.

We educated over 300 children from that Marceline Elementary and Father McCartan schools. We even had some eager high school classes come down to join in on the fun. We had booths on chemical safety, chickens, turkeys, geese, pigs, cattle, goats, horses, wheat, soybeans, corn, oats, and blueberries. Additionally, the Missouri Soybean Merchandising Council sponsored activity booklets for every student that attended our event to receive.

Hopefully everyone learned a lot and enjoyed the day. Thank you to Marceline high school teachers for allowing my FFA kids to participate and educate our youth about agriculture. Also thank you to the Marceline elementary teachers and teachers at McCartan that took time out of their daily schedule to come to our event. We appreciate all the support that helped make this event such a success.

FFA members who wore complete FFA Official Dress all day were rewarded with a free pizza lunch in the Ag room. 20 of our members participated in wearing their FFA Official Dress, and they all looked very sharp!

post_text:
Today for FFA Week it was Greenhand/'Mercia day. Greenhand students (or first year FFA members) dyed hands green and got to put their green handprint on the Greenhand wall in the Ag room. We also cooked Cherry Turnovers for Teacher appreciation tomorrow.
Fun FFA Week fact for everyone: National FFA Week is held during George Washington's Birthday week every year in honor of him being our first President and also very farming oriented. There is a myth George Washington cut down a cherry tree. Thus, the turnovers we made are cherry filled to honor him and just because it's a fun fact. If you would like to read more about it Mt Vernon had an article on it at the following link: http://www.mountvernon.org/digital-encyclopedia/article/cherry-tree-myth/.

post_text: Marceline FFA was honored to host Audrey Martin as a guest speaker on February 14th. Audrey is originally from the Meadville FFA Chapter. She currently serves as a Missouri FFA State Vice President and attends the University of Missouri to become an agriculture teacher. She is one of only sixteen MO State FFA Officers across the state of Missouri. The state of Missouri is comprised of 25,375 FFA members and 347 FFA chapters. Audrey's topics of discussion with students included teamwork, goal planning, and information about the FFA organization.

post_text: Congratulations to Rhiannon Niemeier and Luke Vaughn for their placings at the Area III FFA Proficiency Screening tonight. Rhiannon Niemeier placed 3rd in Vegetable Production, Entrepreneurship; and Luke Vaughn placed 6th in Beef Production, Entrepreneurship. Rhiannon will walk across stage at Area III Banquet in the spring to receive her 3rd place award. Both will also be the Marceline winners of these areas awarded for our chapter proficiencies at banquet. 24 schools are in Area III and can bring one application each to compete in each proficiency area. Great job to both on their hard work!

post_text: Area III FFA Leadership Conference was held at Schuyler County High School Sept. 12th. Marceline’s own Rhiannon Niemeier, the Area III FFA Student Secretary, and Nora Dodd, one of the Area III FFA Advisors, helped plan the evening’s events.The leadership conference helped students to further their leadership skills in their communities. Participants took part in leadership break-out sessions, icebreakers, and prepared for their futures while attending the college fair. Those in attendance also had the opportunity to listen to the Director of Agriculture, Chris Chinn; Missouri’s national FFA officer candidate, Sydnee Mason; and one of the Missouri State FFA Officers, Audrey Martin speak. All students left with more knowledge to apply to their daily lives and communities.

post_text: Marceline FFA Ag Science II and a few upper class men attended the MU Forage Systems Research Center Field Day at Linneus, MO today. Students learned about winter feeding options to help cow-calf producers through drought induced feed shortages, forage nutritive values of common pasture weeds, stretching winter stockpile resources, managing timber resources during drought, sunn hemp/tall fescue pasture grazing options, the economic impact of drought on livestock operations, information on Missouri drought and how all Missourians can participate in the drought assessment process, and USDA programs to help farmers. At the end of the field day each participant was served a complimentary brisket meal. Students learned a lot and had a great time.

The Marceline FFA Trap Team traveled three hours to Linn Creek on Saturday, September 8th. It rained the whole time we were there, but that didn't stop us!

The Girls team consisting of Ashlynne Wright, Mackenzie Slater, Veronica Vaughn, Sevilla Bussman, and Kaileen Gibson placed 3rd place overall in the ladies division and will be receiving medals and a trophy to commemorate this honor. There were 69 competitors in this division. They were very proud!

The Boys teams did not place. They were competing against 258 other competitors.

Each team member shot at 100 clay pigeons each. The scores are as follows.

Top 2 shooters:
Grahm Johnson: 92
Wesley Baldwin: 89

Girls Team:

Mackenzie Slater: 77

Veronica Vaughn: 74
Kaileen Gibson: 12

350/500 team score

post_text: Rhiannon Niemeier, Area III FFA Secretary, and Miss Dodd, one of the Area III FFA Advisors, braved the heat June 8-9th at the Area Officer Institute (AOI) at Camp Rising Sun at Lake of the Ozarks. They perfected their leadership skills with the rest of the Area III FFA officer team. This officer team is comprised of elected student officers from different schools in Area III and three appointed Area III FFA Advisors. They are in charge of planning all Area III FFA events. While at AOI they had the opportunity to meet and interact with the 15 other officer teams from across the state of Missouri.

post_text: Our FFA members have very busy summers, but that didn't stop a group of them from braving the heat this last Friday at our June FFA Meeting. post_text: Day two of State FFA Convention was a success. Students attended leadership workshops, the career fair, and were able to listen to guest speaker Carey Portell. They had the opportunity to mingle and network at this year's convention which had an outstanding attendance of 9,718! At the second session, Rhiannon Niemeier and Bailee Gerdes wowed the crowd with their performance on the main stage of the Hearnes. Rhiannon played the ukulele while Bailee sang "Jolene" by Dolly Parton. Additionally, two of our members, Dalton Cordray and Bailee Gerdes, were awarded their State FFA degrees. Only 716 members received their State FFA Degrees this year out of the 25,920 members across the state. Marceline FFA had a very eventful and successful trip to convention. Great job to all!

post_text: Monday night Bailee Gerdes competed at the NE District FFA Leadership Development Event (LDE) Competition at Monroe City, MO. The NE FFA District spans three FFA areas all of which have approximately 20+ schools in them. She was one of only nine individuals in the NE District who had advanced past area competitions in Job Interview to compete at the District level. Although she did not advance to the state competition (only three from the NE District go) making it to District competition is a worthwhile accomplishment and took many hours of preparation. If you see her please applaud her on her efforts.

Then, only five academy members are selected from each of the six districts to make up the academy. Luke did not make it into the academy but making it into the top 60 in the state is impressive. Good job!

post_text: Last night were the Area III officer interviews. The 24 schools from our area, Area III, can bring one candidate and two voting delegates. Our chapter's candidate was Rhiannon Niemeier and our voting delegates were Luke Vaughn and Madison Gerdes. After two rounds of interviews, Rhiannon Niemeier was selected to serve as the Area III Secretary for the 2018-19 year which also means Marceline's Ag Instructor, Miss Dodd, will serve as one of the three area FFA advisors this coming year to oversee the Area III officer team. Both Rhiannon and Miss Dodd will work throughout the year helping plan and execute all Area III FFA events including Battle of the Chapters, Greenhand Motivational Conference, Leadership Conference, Banquet, etc. Congratulations Rhiannon Niemeier. Marceline FFA is very proud of you!

post_text: Luke Vaughn has been selected as a Northeast District semi-finalist by the Missouri Agribusiness Academy Written Review Committee. He had sent in an extensive application to get to this point. Oral interviews are the next step in determining the 2018 Missouri Agribusiness Academy class. Luke will interview at the Northeast District interviews on Tuesday, March 13, 2018. Interviews are conducted by a panel of three judges who represent various facets of Missouri agriculture. Five 2018 Missouri Agribusiness Academy members will be selected from the Northeast District by combining interview and written application scores. If selected as one of these five from our district, Luke will be one of only 30 sophomore students across the entire state of Missouri attending this conference. If you see him please wish him luck as he prepares for this endeavor!
